<%- include('partials/head', { title: 'Brand' }) %>
<%- include('partials/nav') %>

<div class="page">
<section class="page-section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="page-header a-fade-up" style="max-width:720px;">
      <div class="section-tag">Brand</div>
      <h2>How perch. looks, sounds, and shows up.</h2>
      <p>This is the living guide for anyone creating on behalf of perch. — copy, design, product, or otherwise. It's short because the brand is simple.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="privacy-body a-fade-up">
      <div class="privacy-block">
        <h3>Wordmark</h3>
        <p>The name is always lowercase, always followed by a full stop. The dot is the full stop — not a decorative mark, not a bullet point. It's a statement: we finish our sentences.</p>
        <div style="margin-top:16px;padding:24px;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:var(--radius);background:var(--bg);">
          <img src="/wordmark.svg" alt="perch. wordmark" style="height:40px;">
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top:10px;display:flex;gap:20px;flex-wrap:wrap;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-dim);">
          <span>Font: Georgia / serif italic</span>
          <span>Weight: Regular</span>
          <span>Dot: accent gold <span style="display:inline-block;width:10px;height:10px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--accent);vertical-align:middle;"></span></span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-block">
        <h3>Name usage</h3>
        <p>Always lowercase, always with the dot. Not <em>Perch</em>, not <em>perch</em>, not <em>the perch app</em>. Just <strong>perch.</strong> at the start of a sentence too — the dot is part of the name, not punctuation.</p>
        <div class="brand-example good">perch. catches the price change before it hits your bank.</div>
        <div class="brand-example bad">Perch is the best way to manage your subscriptions!</div>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-block">
        <h3>Voice principles</h3>
        <div class="brand-voice-grid">
          <div class="brand-voice-item">
            <div class="brand-voice-heading">Smart, not smug</div>
            <p>We know things. We don't flex. The tone is someone who's done the research and can explain it over a drink — not a lecturer.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="brand-voice-item">
            <div class="brand-voice-heading">Restrained, not sparse</div>
            <p>We say what needs saying and stop. No filler adjectives, no "revolutionary" claims, no "game-changing." If something is good, we state it plainly.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="brand-voice-item">
            <div class="brand-voice-heading">Slightly dry, not cold</div>
            <p>A little wit goes a long way. We can be funny about the absurdity of auto-renewal without being a comedy account. The humour is in the observation, not the punchline.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="brand-voice-item">
            <div class="brand-voice-heading">Anti-fintech-bro, not anti-business</div>
            <p>We're critical of the VC-funded "move fast and break your trust" model. We're not anti-profit or anti-growth. We just think there's a better way to build.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-block">
        <h3>Colour palette</h3>
        <div class="brand-swatches">
          <div class="brand-swatch">
            <div style="background:#0a0e0d;height:60px;border-radius:8px 8px 0 0;"></div>
            <div style="background:#0e1211;height:60px;border-radius:0 0 8px 8px;border-top:1px solid var(--line);"></div>
            <div class="brand-swatch-label">Backgrounds</div>
            <div class="brand-swatch-val">#0a0e0d / #0e1211</div>
          </div>
          <div class="brand-swatch">
            <div style="background:#141917;height:120px;border-radius:8px;"></div>
            <div class="brand-swatch-label">Panels</div>
            <div class="brand-swatch-val">#141917</div>
          </div>
          <div class="brand-swatch">
            <div style="background:#edefed;height:120px;border-radius:8px;"></div>
            <div class="brand-swatch-label">Text</div>
            <div class="brand-swatch-val">#edefed</div>
          </div>
          <div class="brand-swatch">
            <div style="background:#a3aba7;height:120px;border-radius:8px;"></div>
            <div class="brand-swatch-label">Text dim</div>
            <div class="brand-swatch-val">#a3aba7</div>
          </div>
          <div class="brand-swatch">
            <div style="background:#64706a;height:120px;border-radius:8px;"></div>
            <div class="brand-swatch-label">Text faint</div>
            <div class="brand-swatch-val">#64706a</div>
          </div>
          <div class="brand-swatch">
            <div style="background:#c98a3a;height:120px;border-radius:8px;"></div>
            <div class="brand-swatch-label">Accent</div>
            <div class="brand-swatch-val">#c98a3a</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-block">
        <h3>Typography</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom:6px;"><strong style="font-family:var(--serif);font-size:28px;">Serif</strong> — Iowan Old Style, Palatino, Georgia. Used for headings and the wordmark. Editorial, warm, authoritative.</p>
        <p><strong style="font-size:16px;">Sans</strong> — Inter, system UI stack. Used for body text, UI, everything else. Clean, neutral, gets out of the way.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-block">
        <h3>Copy patterns</h3>
        <div class="brand-pattern">
          <div class="brand-pattern-heading">Headlines</div>
          <p class="brand-pattern-example">“Stop paying for things you forgot you agreed to.”</p>
          <p>Declarative. Slightly provocative but true. Never a question. Never a command disguised as curiosity.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="brand-pattern">
          <div class="brand-pattern-heading">Subheadings</div>
          <p class="brand-pattern-example">“Four steps. No dashboards to maintain, no accounts to link.”</p>
          <p>Facts. Periods. The benefit stated as a simple reality, not a promise.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="brand-pattern">
          <div class="brand-pattern-heading">Body copy</div>
          <p class="brand-pattern-example">“Every provider you deal with is incentivised to make renewal silent and cancellation slow.”</p>
          <p>Direct. One idea per sentence. No jargon. Trust the reader to keep up.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="brand-pattern">
          <div class="brand-pattern-heading">Objection handling</div>
          <p class="brand-pattern-example">“We don't act on your behalf, ever. You get the verdict and the deadline. You make the call.”</p>
          <p>Address the fear directly. Explain why it's not a limitation — it's the point. End with agency.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-block">
        <h3>Never say</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Revolutionary, game-changing, disruptive, innovative (you don't get to call yourself these)</li>
          <li>Leverage, optimise, holistic, ecosystem (fintech jargon)</li>
          <li>"Take control of your finances" (too broad, sounds like every other app)</li>
          <li>Exclamation marks in body copy (one per page max, and only if it's genuinely surprising)</li>
          <li>Emojis in product copy (they're fine on social. Nowhere near pricing, privacy, or the product.)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
</div>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
